President Obama has declared a major disaster in Connecticut due to the impact of Tropical Storm Irene. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Gary Stanley has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional counties may receive assistance after damage assessments are completed. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.